when you export the canvas as a blob it will always default to being a png format

So you could as well write:
```
function canvas2Image() {
    canvas.toBlob(function (blob) {
        saveAs(blob, imageName+".png");
    });
}
```

But if you now would like to save it as a JPEG then you would have to do:

function canvas2Image() {
    canvas.toBlob(function (blob) {
        saveAs(blob, imageName+".jpg");
    }, "image/jpeg");
}

