You are correct that a Python & maps to a C && and | -> ||.  These are the operations in interp_body.cpp:

        case OP_AND_BBB: VEC_ARG2(b_dest = (b1 && b2));
        case OP_OR_BBB: VEC_ARG2(b_dest = (b1 || b2));

There's no more space in the ascii wordspace for more operations to be added.  I'm actively working on NumExpr3 which will have a 4-byte wordspace in which case I have bitwise `&` and `|`whereas `and` maps to `&&`  and `or` to `||`.  It's a big project though...

